{"question_id": "syn-pdfQA/03_Raw_Question_Answer_Data/research articles/2510.22211v1_rawQA.json#1", "question": "What are the main features observed in the HST UV spectrum of Ansky, and how do they compare to typical AGN spectra?", "answers": ["The HST UV spectrum of Ansky shows a steep power-law slope of f_λ ∝ λ^{-2.6}, which is much steeper than the typical AGN index of -1.5. No broad emission lines characteristic of Type 1 AGNs are detected; instead, only narrow absorption lines such as Lyα, N V λ1240, and C IV λ1549 are present, likely due to host-galaxy gas. The spectrum is best described by a high-temperature, featureless blackbody transient, and the absence of spectral lines further disfavors the AGN scenario."], "prediction": "The HST UV spectrum of Ansky is characterized as featureless, lacking broad emission lines typical of AGNs, and instead shows a steep power-law continuum with a spectral index of -2.6. This contrasts sharply with typical AGN spectra, which exhibit prominent broad emission lines such as Lyα, N V λ1240, and C IV λ1549. The absence of these features strongly disfavors the turn-on AGN scenario for Ansky", "raw_answer": "The HST UV spectrum of Ansky is characterized as featureless, lacking broad emission lines typical of AGNs, and instead shows a steep power-law continuum with a spectral index of -2.6. This contrasts sharply with typical AGN spectra, which exhibit prominent broad emission lines such as Lyα, N V λ1240, and C IV λ1549. The absence of these features strongly disfavors the turn-on AGN scenario for Ansky.\n\n引用页码与关键关系: 页码 [4, 5, 6, 11] 关键关系: keyword::featureless_tde --[keyword_hit]--> 2510_22211v1_page4_text_2; keyword::agn --[keyword_hit]--> 2510_22211v1_page4_text_3; keyword::featureless_tde --[keyword_hit]--> 2510_22211v1_page11_conclusion_0", "source_hint": "2510.22211v1.pdf", "doc_name": "2510.22211v1.pdf", "category": "syn", "dataset": "03_Raw_Question_Answer_Data", "question_type": "unknown", "evidence_pages": [], "pages